HEADWORD: Streel
<hw>Streel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Stroll</er>.]</ety> <def>To trail along; to saunter or be drawn
along, carelessly, swaying in a kind of zigzag motion.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

